      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "Can you clarify why this needs to be moved? Using master (661fe5d65cc6516439f9d6e0f1a5e2db0e129059) I can do:\r\n```bash\r\n./autogen.sh\r\n./configure --with-bignum=gmp\r\n....\r\n  asm                     = x86_64\r\n  bignum                  = gmp\r\n  ecmult window size      = 15\r\n```\r\nand secp256k1 is configured with bignum support using gmp. I guess there's somewhere this doesn't currently work?\r\n\r\n@sipa also [mentioned on IRC](http://www.erisian.com.au/bitcoin-core-dev/log-2020-10-11.html#l-187):\r\n> 2020-10-11T16:16:27  <sipa> luke-jr: fwiw, after [secp256k1 PR 767](https://github.com/bitcoin-core/secp256k1/pull/767) we'll probably remove bignum support entirely",
